<paragraph blockId="9.[136,1452,1349,1952]" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">
<emphasis box="[189,329,1457,1483]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Fungicolous</emphasis>
, growing on a fruiting body of 
<taxonomicName box="[682,805,1457,1483]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Boletaceae</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[848,1040,1457,1484]" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Asexual morph:</emphasis>
Hyphomycetous. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" box="[1245,1360,1457,1483]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">Mycelium</taxonomicName>
forms a loosely attached layer on the fruiting body of the host (
<figureCitation box="[738,876,1494,1520]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,200,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[198,1389,190,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypomyces sichuanensis (CGMCC 3.20159). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d, e, g Conidiophores. f Phialides. h, i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. k Aleurioconidia. j Conidiogeous cell. l Phialoconidia. Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–j = 20 μm, k, l = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316528/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">FIGURE 3a</figureCitation>
). On PDA medium, colony tomentose to pubescent, white at the beginning, then becoming yellow (
<figureCitation box="[667,836,1529,1556]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,200,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[198,1389,190,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypomyces sichuanensis (CGMCC 3.20159). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d, e, g Conidiophores. f Phialides. h, i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. k Aleurioconidia. j Conidiogeous cell. l Phialoconidia. Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–j = 20 μm, k, l = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316528/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">FIGURE 3b, c</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" box="[857,967,1529,1555]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[857,967,1529,1555]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Mycelium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficial, developing as floccose masses of septate, branched, smooth and hyaline hyphae bearing robust conidiophores with golden yellow spore masses (
<figureCitation box="[143,283,1601,1628]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,200,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[198,1389,190,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypomyces sichuanensis (CGMCC 3.20159). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d, e, g Conidiophores. f Phialides. h, i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. k Aleurioconidia. j Conidiogeous cell. l Phialoconidia. Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–j = 20 μm, k, l = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316528/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">FIGURE 3b</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[302,467,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Conidiophores</emphasis>
hyaline, erect, flexuous, septate, smooth. With 
<specimenCount box="[988,1094,1602,1628]" pageId="9" pageNumber="37" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
of 
<emphasis box="[1128,1348,1601,1627]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
phialidic and aleuriogenic (
<figureCitation box="[338,502,1637,1664]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,200,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[198,1389,190,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypomyces sichuanensis (CGMCC 3.20159). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d, e, g Conidiophores. f Phialides. h, i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. k Aleurioconidia. j Conidiogeous cell. l Phialoconidia. Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–j = 20 μm, k, l = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316528/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">FIGURE 3d–i</figureCitation>
). 
<typeStatus box="[522,578,1638,1664]" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Type</typeStatus>
A: 
<emphasis box="[621,727,1637,1663]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Phialides</emphasis>
in 2–3 verticels, or solitary, 65–180 × 2–3 μm (= 115 × 2.5 μm, n = 30), attenuating to 1.0–2.0 μm at their apices (
<figureCitation box="[707,888,1673,1700]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,200,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[198,1389,190,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypomyces sichuanensis (CGMCC 3.20159). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d, e, g Conidiophores. f Phialides. h, i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. k Aleurioconidia. j Conidiogeous cell. l Phialoconidia. Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–j = 20 μm, k, l = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316528/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">FIGURE 3d–f j</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[910,1069,1673,1699]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Phialoconidia</emphasis>
acrogenous, hyaline, thin 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1360,1369,1674,1700]" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">-</emphasis>
walled, ellipsoid to clavate, aseptate, 11.5–18 × 3–6 μm (= 14.5 × 5 μm, n = 50) (
<figureCitation box="[955,1089,1709,1736]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,200,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[198,1389,190,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypomyces sichuanensis (CGMCC 3.20159). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d, e, g Conidiophores. f Phialides. h, i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. k Aleurioconidia. j Conidiogeous cell. l Phialoconidia. Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–j = 20 μm, k, l = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316528/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">FIGURE 3l</figureCitation>
). 
<typeStatus box="[1110,1166,1710,1736]" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Type</typeStatus>
B: 
<emphasis box="[1206,1351,1709,1735]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Aleuriogenic</emphasis>
discrete, on short or long side branches (
<figureCitation box="[493,685,1745,1772]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,200,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[198,1389,190,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypomyces sichuanensis (CGMCC 3.20159). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d, e, g Conidiophores. f Phialides. h, i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. k Aleurioconidia. j Conidiogeous cell. l Phialoconidia. Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–j = 20 μm, k, l = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316528/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">FIGURE 3d, h, i</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[709,877,1745,1771]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Aleurioconidia</emphasis>
hyaline at the beginning, becoming golden yellow when mature, subglobose to globose, thick 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[622,631,1782,1808]" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">-</emphasis>
walled, aseptate, with angular tubercles on surface, 8.5–15.5 × 8–15 μm (12.5 × 12 μm, n = 50) (
<figureCitation box="[433,635,1817,1844]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,200,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[198,1389,190,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypomyces sichuanensis (CGMCC 3.20159). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d, e, g Conidiophores. f Phialides. h, i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. k Aleurioconidia. j Conidiogeous cell. l Phialoconidia. Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–j = 20 μm, k, l = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316528/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">FIGURE 3h, i, k</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis box="[659,767,1817,1843]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Tubercles</emphasis>
densely, cylindrical, 1–2 μm, often with apical depression (
<figureCitation box="[143,285,1853,1880]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1881,1903]" captionTargetBox="[210,1377,200,1851]" captionTargetId="figure-19@10.[198,1389,190,1857]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 3. Hypomyces sichuanensis (CGMCC 3.20159). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d, e, g Conidiophores. f Phialides. h, i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. k Aleurioconidia. j Conidiogeous cell. l Phialoconidia. Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–j = 20 μm, k, l = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316528" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316528/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">FIGURE 3k</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[305,661,1853,1880]" pageId="9" pageNumber="37">Sexual morph: Undetermined</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
