<paragraph blockId="11.[136,1452,158,508]" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis box="[189,253,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">Notes</emphasis>
:—The new species grows on fruiting bodies of 
<taxonomicName box="[807,930,158,184]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Boletaceae</taxonomicName>
sp. containing only the asexual state. Among the known Boleticolous species of 
<taxonomicName box="[531,660,195,220]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[531,660,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">Hypomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jing Z. Sun" authorityYear="2021" box="[675,853,194,221]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[675,695,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[710,853,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Tul. &amp; C. Tul." authorityName="Tul. &amp; C. Tul." class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chrysospermus">
<emphasis box="[1196,1216,195,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1231,1399,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">chrysospermus</emphasis>
Tul. &amp; C. Tul.
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Rogerson &amp; Samuels" authorityName="Rogerson &amp; Samuels" box="[265,716,230,257]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="microspermus">
<emphasis box="[265,460,231,256]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">H. microspermus</emphasis>
Rogerson &amp; Samuels
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sahr et Ammer" authorityName="Sahr et Ammer" box="[780,1237,230,257]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Sepedonium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="laevigatum">
<emphasis box="[780,1050,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">Sepedonium laevigatum</emphasis>
Sahr et Ammer
</taxonomicName>
in forming poorly developed verticills conidiophores and the shape and size of aleurioconidia (
<bibRefCitation author="Rogerson, C. T. &amp; Samuels, G. J." box="[1004,1314,266,292]" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" pagination="413 - 432" refId="ref7838" refString="Rogerson, C. T. &amp; Samuels, G. J. (1989) Boleticolous species of Hypomyces. Mycologia 81 (3): 413 - 432. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1989.12025764" type="journal article" year="1989">Rogerson &amp; Samuels 1989</bibRefCitation>
). Compared with 
<taxonomicName box="[197,403,302,329]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chrysospermus">
<emphasis box="[197,217,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[235,403,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">chrysospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[421,617,303,328]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="microspermus">
<emphasis box="[421,617,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">H. microspermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[686,842,302,329]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Sepedonium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="laevigatum">
<emphasis box="[686,700,303,329]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[718,842,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">laevigatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, aleuriospores and phialoconidia of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jing Z. Sun" authorityYear="2021" box="[1270,1451,302,329]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[1270,1290,303,328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1308,1451,302,328]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
averaged somewhat smaller than those of 
<taxonomicName box="[617,821,338,365]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="chrysospermus">
<emphasis box="[617,637,339,364]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[653,821,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">chrysospermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(14–21 μm for aleuriospores, and 5–27 × 3–11 μm for phialoconidia) and 
<taxonomicName box="[354,507,374,401]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Sepedonium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="laevigatum">
<emphasis box="[354,368,375,401]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[383,507,374,400]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">laevigatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(14–19 μm for Aleuriospores, and 8–24 × 3.5–9.5 μm for phialoconidia) but larger than that of 
<taxonomicName box="[276,471,411,436]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="microspermus">
<emphasis box="[276,471,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">H. microspermus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(9–15 μm for Aleuriospores, and 6.4–11.7 × 4–6.5 μm for phialoconidia) (
<bibRefCitation author="Sahr, T. &amp; Ammer, H. &amp; Besl H. &amp; Fischer M." pageId="11" pageNumber="39" pagination="935 - 943" refId="ref8203" refString="Sahr, T., Ammer, H., Besl H. &amp; Fischer M. (1999) Infrageneric classification of the boleticolous genus Sepedonium: species delimitation and phylogenetic relationships. Mycologia 91 (6): 935 - 943. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1999.12061104" type="journal article" year="1999">
Sahr 
<emphasis box="[1393,1452,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<tableCitation box="[205,317,446,472]" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="9.[136,224,159,183]" captionText="TABLE 2. Comparison of morphological characteristics of the new species and closely allied taxa." pageId="11" pageNumber="39">TABLE 2</tableCitation>
). Additionally, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jing Z. Sun" authorityYear="2021" box="[490,667,446,473]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sichuanensis">
<emphasis box="[490,510,447,472]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[524,667,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">sichuanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[866,1018,446,473]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Sepedonium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="laevigatum">
<emphasis box="[866,880,447,473]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[894,1018,446,472]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">laevigatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by no yellow discoloration of medium (
<bibRefCitation author="Sahr, T. &amp; Ammer, H. &amp; Besl H. &amp; Fischer M." box="[144,327,482,508]" pageId="11" pageNumber="39" pagination="935 - 943" refId="ref8203" refString="Sahr, T., Ammer, H., Besl H. &amp; Fischer M. (1999) Infrageneric classification of the boleticolous genus Sepedonium: species delimitation and phylogenetic relationships. Mycologia 91 (6): 935 - 943. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1999.12061104" type="journal article" year="1999">
Sahr 
<emphasis box="[204,260,482,508]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="39">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
